-- Peru Stocks: Atacocha, Candente, Ferreyros, Minera IRL, Rio Alto
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-04T21:18:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/peru-stocks-atacocha-candente-ferreyros-minera-irl-rio-alto.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m. local time.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  gained 0.3 percent to 19,940.09. The
 MSCI All Peru Capped Index (MXPECAPD)  rose 0.1 percent to 2,572.26.  Rio Alto Mining Ltd. (RIO)  , a Canadian gold miner, rose
7.2 percent to $3.41, a four-week high, after announcing it
produced 51,398 ounces of gold during its first full year of
operation.  Ferreyros SA (FERREYC1)  (FERREYC1 PE), the Lima-based distributor for
Caterpillar Inc., climbed 1.7 percent to 2.34 soles after
announcing sales jumped 40 percent to $1.4 billion last year.  Miners slumped after metals dropped in  New York  and  London ,
said Eduardo Fernandini, a trader at Lima-based brokerage Kallpa
Securities SAB.  Minera IRL Ltd. (MIRL)  , a U.K. minerals explorer with a
gold mine in Peru, dropped 5.6 percent to $1.02.  Cia. Minera
Atacocha SA (CMA\B)  (ATACOBC1 PE), the Lima-based zinc mining company,
fell 2.5 percent to 79 centimos.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  ,
a Canadian exploration company, declined 2 percent to 96 cents.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 Alex Emery  in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
